<div style="position: relative; height: 15px; width: 100%;">  <a style="float: right;" href="?subtopic=creatures&race=elfscout">next <img src="images/arrow_right.gif" width="15" height="11" border="0"/></a>  <a style="position: absolute;" href="?subtopic=creatures&race=elephant"><img src="images/arrow_left.gif" width="15" height="11" border="0"/> previous</a>  <div style="position: absolute; width: 80%; margin-left: 10%; margin-right: 10%; text-align: center;"><a href="?subtopic=creatures"><img src="images/arrow_up.gif" width="11" height="15" border="0"/> back</a></div></div><div style="position: relative; top: 25px; clear: both; "><div style="height: 64px; margin-bottom: 5px;">  <h2 style="float: right;">Elf Arcanists</h2>  <img src="images/library/elfarcanist.gif"/></div><div style="margin-bottom: 35px; clear: both;">  <p>Elf Arcanists are the military guides of the elves. They belong to the martial caste, the Kuridai, and all of them are very suspicious against any intruder. They are the strongest fighters among the elves, know to handle several distance fighting weapons, and are very skilled in magic. They can even heal themselves.</p>  <p>Elf Arcanists have 220 hitpoints. They are strong against death, energy and fire damage. On the other hand, they are weak against holy damage. These creatures can neither be summoned nor convinced. In addition, they are able to sense invisible creatures.</p>  <p>Elf Arcanists yield 175 experience points. They carry blank runes, breads, elvish talismans, gold coins, melons, scrolls and sometimes other items with them.</p>  </div></div>